Package stincmale.ratmex.meter

Class ConcurrentRateMeterConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.meter.RateMeterConfig
      • stincmale.ratmex.meter.ConcurrentRateMeterConfig

  • @Immutable
public class ConcurrentRateMeterConfig
extends RateMeterConfig
    A configuration that can be used to create concurrent implementations of AbstractRateMeter, e.g. ConcurrentNavigableMapRateMeter, ConcurrentRingBufferRateMeter.

    The default values:

    • The default values from RateMeterConfig except for RateMeterConfig.getTicksCounterSupplier(), RateMeterConfig.getHistoryLength()
    • RateMeterConfig.getTicksCounterSupplier() - LongAdderTicksCounter::new
    • RateMeterConfig.getHistoryLength() - 64
    • getMaxTicksCountAttempts() - 16
    • getMode() - ConcurrentRateMeterConfig.Mode.STRICT
    • isCollectStats() - false
    • getWaitStrategySupplier() - YieldWaitStrategy::instance
    • getLockStrategySupplier() - new SpinLockStrategy(YieldWaitStrategy.instance())

      • getMaxTicksCountAttempts

        public final int getMaxTicksCountAttempts​()
        Specifies the desired maximum number of attempts to calculate the number of ticks (see RateMeter.ticksCount() for example). Note that this is just a hint, so an implementation may choose to do more attempts, but the number of attempts must be finite.

        The reasoning behind this hint
        Implementations may allow a race condition (for performance reasons) while counting ticks. When running out of the number of attempts such implementations may choose to fall over to an approach that excludes the race and allows to eventually count the ticks.
